# Database & SQL Patterns

## Supabase Client

Always use the configured client from [src/lib/supabase.ts](mdc:src/lib/supabase.ts):

```typescript
import { supabase } from '@/lib/supabase'

// Query with proper typing
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from('table_name')
  .select('*')
  .eq('column', value)

// Always check for errors
if (error) {
  console.error('Database error:', error)
  return NextResponse.json({ error: error.message }, { status: 500 })
}
```

## JSONB Storage Pattern

Questions stored as JSONB in `question_bank` table:

```sql
CREATE TABLE question_bank (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  question_data JSONB NOT NULL,        -- Full Question object
  question_text TEXT NOT NULL,         -- Searchable text
  question_type TEXT NOT NULL,         -- For filtering
  unit_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  lesson_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  topics TEXT[] DEFAULT '{}',
  difficulty TEXT CHECK (difficulty IN ('easy', 'medium', 'hard')),
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

## Row Level Security (RLS)

Current migration: [supabase/migrations/enable_rls_security.sql](mdc:supabase/migrations/enable_rls_security.sql)

### RLS Pattern for Tables
```sql
-- Enable RLS
ALTER TABLE table_name ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- Admin/Teacher access
CREATE POLICY "Admins and teachers can manage"
ON table_name
FOR ALL
TO authenticated
USING (
  auth.jwt() ->> 'email' IN (
    SELECT email FROM admin_emails
    UNION
    SELECT email FROM teacher_emails
  )
);

-- Student read access
CREATE POLICY "Students can view own data"
ON table_name
FOR SELECT
TO authenticated
USING (user_id = auth.uid());
```

## Performance Optimizations

From [supabase/migrations/optimize_rls_performance.sql](mdc:supabase/migrations/optimize_rls_performance.sql):

### Indexes
```sql
-- Text search
CREATE INDEX idx_question_text_search 
ON question_bank USING gin(to_tsvector('english', question_text));

-- Filtering columns
CREATE INDEX idx_unit_lesson 
ON question_bank (unit_id, lesson_id);

-- Common queries
CREATE INDEX idx_difficulty_published 
ON assignments (difficulty, published) WHERE published = true;
```

### Materialized Views
```sql
-- Pre-compute expensive queries
CREATE MATERIALIZED VIEW student_progress_summary AS
SELECT 
  student_id,
  COUNT(*) as total_assignments,
  AVG(score) as average_score
FROM submissions
GROUP BY student_id;

-- Refresh strategy
REFRESH MATERIALIZED VIEW CONCURRENTLY student_progress_summary;
```

## Query Patterns

### Filtering with Supabase
```typescript
// Dynamic query building
let query = supabase
  .from('question_bank')
  .select('*')
  .order('created_at', { ascending: false })

// Apply filters conditionally
if (unitId) query = query.eq('unit_id', unitId)
if (difficulty) query = query.eq('difficulty', difficulty)
if (topics?.length) query = query.contains('topics', topics)
if (searchText) query = query.ilike('question_text', `%${searchText}%`)

const { data, error } = await query
```

### Joins and Relations
```typescript
// Join with related tables
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('assignments')
  .select(`
    *,
    lesson:lessons(id, title, slug),
    submissions:assignment_submissions(*)
  `)
  .eq('published', true)
```

## Function Security

From [supabase/migrations/fix_function_search_paths.sql](mdc:supabase/migrations/fix_function_search_paths.sql):

```sql
-- Set proper search path for security
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION function_name()
RETURNS type
LANGUAGE plpgsql
SECURITY DEFINER
SET search_path = public, auth
AS $$
BEGIN
  -- Function logic
END;
$$;
```

